22 September 2016Government embarked on a third year anniversary of the Thusong Service Center Annual Week from Monday, 19 September 2016. The closing event of the week will take place on the Friday, 23 September 2016 at KwaZanele Community Hall, Breyten in Mpumalanga Province.The campaign was running the whole week under the theme: Moving the Public Service Forward: We Belong, We Care, We Serve .Members of the media are invited to the closing event as follows:Part one: Service delivery walk about and visit to the clinic Date: Friday, 23 September 2016 Time: 9h45 Venue: Breyten Thusong Service CenterPart Two: Community Imbizo/ service delivery on wheels Date: Friday, 23 September 2016 Time: 11h00 Venue: KwaZanele Community Hall, MpumalangaThe Annual Thusong Service Centre Week was piloted in September 2014 aiming at highlighting government services offered at Thusong Service Centres countrywide. This year s Annual Thusong Service Centre Week has been celebrated in line with the Public Service month and highlighted the importance of the Public Service Month in promoting Batho Pele principles. The week also focused on strengthening partnership with all stakeholders and promote the significant of integrated service delivery approach.RSVPs: Poppy Maluka Cell: 071 606 3998 E-mail: poppy@gcis.gov.zaEnquires: Jerry Nkosi Cell: 076 593 4586 E-mail: jerry@gcis.gov.zaIssued by Government Comunication and Information Systems